      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Of course, I can certainly help you craft that email! It's a delicate balance, and I know how important it is to maintain a positive relationship with the candidate.\n\nHere is a template that strikes that balance, complete with a few notes on how to weave in the \"goblin\" perspective to keep the tone light but professional:\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Application for [Job Title]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well and that you are enjoying your time away from the office!\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the [Job Title] position at [Company Name]. After reviewing the final round of interviews, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has truly resonated with our team's vision.\n\nWhile this is a difficult decision for us, I wanted to share this with you because I believe you are a very talented and enthusiastic individual. We have been following your work closely, and we are confident that your skills will be incredibly valuable to our team once you join us.\n\nWe would love to continue our conversation about how your background aligns with our future projects. Please let me know if you are open to a brief call next week to discuss this",
