      "content": "Understood. No goblins, no metaphors, no extra fluff. Just a clean, professional template for a rejection email.\n\nHere is a standard, polite, and empathetic version you can use:\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update regarding your application for [Job Title]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for your time and interest in joining our team.\n\nAfter reviewing the final round of interviews, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has demonstrated a strong alignment with our current goals.\n\nWhile this is a difficult decision for us, we wanted to personally reach out to you to let you know that you were a very strong candidate. We are confident that your skills will be incredibly valuable to our team once you join us.\n\nWe would love to continue our conversation about how your background aligns with our future projects. Please let me know if you are open to a brief call next week to discuss this further.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n[Company Name]\n\n***\n\nLet me know if you need any adjustments to this.",
